laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 1.2 cm with wall thickening measuring up to 4 mm and mild associated stranding. There is trace free fluid within the pelvis.

The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. Multiple right-sided hepatic hypodensities are noted, likely representing simple cysts or biliary hamartomas. There is no evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation.
The kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. There is no evidence of focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
